            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1" xml:lang="heb">
                <p><supplied reason="lost">ב</supplied>
                    <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/>
                    <supplied reason="lost">למ</supplied>רחשון שנת <num value="1">2</num> עבידו<lb/>
                    <supplied reason="lost">לבני</supplied>
                        <supplied reason="lost">ג</supplied>ורו חנטן כרן שבעה<lb/>
                    <supplied reason="lost">סאן</supplied>
                        <supplied reason="lost">תר</supplied>תין פל<supplied reason="omitted">ג</supplied>
                    <unclear>ק</unclear>ב</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>[On the x of Ma]rcheshvan, year 2, Ubaydu<lb/>[of the sons of G]uru: wheat, kors,
                    seven;<lb/>[seahs, tw]o; hal&lt;f&gt; a qab.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>Seven kors of wheat is considered to be a significant payment. In the
                    inscription, the scribe has combined the words פלג and  קב into one (פלקב) to
                    mean "half a qab;" the final ב of this word is written with a flourish.</p>
            </div>
